Field Level Security: (FLS)
——————————————————————————————————————————
Object Manager -> the object you want to edit -> fields and relationships -> the field you want to edit -> set FLS

This will show all the profiles and if this field is visible/read only to that profile

Visible: Visible and user can edit
Read Only: Will autoamtically check visible but the user cannot edit

——————————————————————————————————————————
Field level security at the profile level:

You can also do the above in a different way. 

1. Search Profile
2. Select the profile you want to change the FLS
3. Select Object Settings
4. Select the object
5. Edit the field permissions
6. Save
——————————————————————————————————————————
Notes:

This can take a while (5-15 min) for salesforce to update even if you saved it.

'Where is this used' button will show all page layouts this custom field is on
	note: standard fields do not have this option
——————————————————————————————————————————
